"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-breaking-debut-sport-paris-olympics-not-without-questions\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Unless you lived through it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094ideally while wearing parachute pants\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094you might have a hard time fully grasping just how omnipresent breaking was in 1980s pop culture.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 167, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There were movies based on it, likeBeat Street,Breakin\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099and its successor,Breakin\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 2: Electric Boogaloo, whose subtitle has lived on for decades as a punch line for pretty much every sequel made.\", \"from\": 168, \"to\": 366, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 266, \"end\": 274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boogaloo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.512552468237305e-28, \"text\": \"Boogaloo\", \"types\": [\"Q188451\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boogaloo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boogaloo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were obligatory breaking scenes in movies\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094Cocoon,Revenge of the Nerdsand countless others\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094that otherwise had nothing to do with breaking.\", \"from\": 367, \"to\": 514, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The sitcomAlicehad a breaking episode.\", \"from\": 515, \"to\": 553, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Merv Griffin had a crew on his show.\", \"from\": 554, \"to\": 590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 554, \"end\": 566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Merv_Griffin\", \"score\": 0.6170819475671974, \"rank\": 0.6205303103457248, \"text\": \"Merv Griffin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Merv_Griffin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Merv_Griffin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Barney Rubble showed off his moves in a commercial for Cocoa Pebbles.\", \"from\": 591, \"to\": 660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 591, \"end\": 604, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barney_Rubble\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barney Rubble\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barney_Rubble\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barney_Rubble\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It waseverywhere.\", \"from\": 661, \"to\": 678, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Naturally, politicians saw a popular trend and were eager to get in on the action.\", \"from\": 680, \"to\": 762, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So it was that at his second inauguration gala, in January 1985, a tuxedoed Ronald Reagan watched as Jimmy Stewart introduced the New York City Breakers, prompting a nation of viewers to ask themselves,How the hell did we get here?The answer only makes the story stranger (and whiter and older): It was Frank Sinatra\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s idea.\", \"from\": 763, \"to\": 1089, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 839, \"end\": 852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ronald_Reagan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.907090179864282e-19, \"text\": \"Ronald Reagan\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ronald_Reagan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ronald_Reagan\"}, {\"begin\": 864, \"end\": 877, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Stewart\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6383834194945708e-75, \"text\": \"Jimmy Stewart\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Stewart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Stewart\"}, {\"begin\": 893, \"end\": 915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Breakers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"New York City Breakers\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Breakers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Breakers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cFrank was a hoofer,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d says Michael Holman, who founded and managed the group.\", \"from\": 1090, \"to\": 1171, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1121, \"end\": 1135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Holman_(filmmaker)\", \"score\": 0.8846538366151998, \"rank\": 0.0933333333333498, \"text\": \"Michael Holman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Holman_(filmmaker)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Holman_(filmmaker)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cHe came from a tradition where you had to sing and dance.\", \"from\": 1172, \"to\": 1232, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You couldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t just be a singer.\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1265, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He loved us.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Ol\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 Blue Eyes had first encountered the Breakers in late 1983 at the Kennedy Center Honors, where they performed as part of a tribute to the dancer Katherine Dunham.\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1450, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1433, \"end\": 1449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katherine_Dunham\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katherine Dunham\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katherine_Dunham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katherine_Dunham\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When it came time to book acts for Reagan\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s party, Sinatra, who was organizing the event, reached out to Holman.\", \"from\": 1451, \"to\": 1565, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A San Francisco native, Holman had moved to New York City in \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009978 to take a job as a banker.\", \"from\": 1566, \"to\": 1659, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1610, \"end\": 1623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8953911353772197e-34, \"text\": \"New York City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He hated the job but loved the city, where he was becoming a fixture in the downtown art scene while also immersing himself in the nascent world of hip-hop.\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1816, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He started an experimental noise band with artist Jean-Michel Basquiat.\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 1888, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1867, \"end\": 1887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Michel_Basquiat\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.687050895831672e-82, \"text\": \"Jean-Michel Basquiat\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Michel_Basquiat\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Michel_Basquiat\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He took Malcolm McLaren\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094the British impresario who created the Sex Pistols\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094up to the Bronx to meet Afrika Bambaataa.\", \"from\": 1889, \"to\": 2009, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1919, \"end\": 1926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999960377095987, \"rank\": 3.683301989951319e-06, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1978, \"end\": 1983, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.841310220972008e-28, \"text\": \"Bronx\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\"}, {\"begin\": 1992, \"end\": 2008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afrika_Bambaataa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Afrika Bambaataa\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afrika_Bambaataa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afrika_Bambaataa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While running a weekly hip-hop night at an East Village reggae club called Negril, Holman saw the crowd go wild over a breaking battle between two crews, the Floor Masters and the Rock Steady Crew, which gave him the inspiration to form the New York City Breakers.\\u00c2  In less than a year they were booking gigs all over the place.\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2339, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2053, \"end\": 2065, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Village,_Manhattan\", \"score\": 0.9968205661580373, \"rank\": 0.0010645904504647525, \"text\": \"East Village\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Village,_Manhattan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Village,_Manhattan\"}, {\"begin\": 2085, \"end\": 2091, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Negril\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Negril\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Negril\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Negril\"}, {\"begin\": 2190, \"end\": 2206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rock_Steady_Crew\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rock Steady Crew\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rock_Steady_Crew\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rock_Steady_Crew\"}, {\"begin\": 2251, \"end\": 2264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8953911353772197e-34, \"text\": \"New York City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the many TV spots that featured Holman\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s crew was one that aired in 1984.\", \"from\": 2340, \"to\": 2421, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In it, one of the Breakers, a B-Boy named Chino Lopez (better known as Action), threw down a gauntlet: \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cMe and my whole crew, we challenge the 1984 [Olympic] gold medal winners in the floor exercise gymnastics team in a competition.\", \"from\": 2422, \"to\": 2656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2464, \"end\": 2469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chino_cloth\", \"score\": 0.9777109413178614, \"rank\": 0.0227971865076659, \"text\": \"Chino\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chino_cloth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chino_cloth\"}, {\"begin\": 2470, \"end\": 2475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Lopez\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.996595831536177e-28, \"text\": \"Lopez\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Lopez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Lopez\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll see you in L.A.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Lamentably, the world never got to see that showdown, and by the middle of \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009985 the mainstream breaking scene had dried up almost as quickly as it had sprung up.\", \"from\": 2657, \"to\": 2847, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But 40 years later, Action\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s wish has come true.\", \"from\": 2848, \"to\": 2898, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Breaking (it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s breaking, not breakdancing, by the way) is making its Games debut in Paris, but not without questions from those within the community.\", \"from\": 2899, \"to\": 3050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2985, \"end\": 2990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2571388585080665e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Like, does something that started as an art form, born on the streets of the Bronx in the 1970s in a neighborhood that was largely disenfranchised, belong at something as corporate as theOlympics?\", \"from\": 3051, \"to\": 3247, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3128, \"end\": 3133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.841310220972008e-28, \"text\": \"Bronx\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sunny Choi had Olympic dreams as a kid growing up in Louisville, but she saw herself as a gymnast, not a dancer.\", \"from\": 3249, \"to\": 3361, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3255, \"end\": 3259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\", \"score\": 0.9996609991704456, \"rank\": 0.00033911578969275864, \"text\": \"Choi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\"}, {\"begin\": 3302, \"end\": 3312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Louisville\", \"score\": 0.9947229925993292, \"rank\": 0.005304784350547445, \"text\": \"Louisville\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Louisville\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Louisville\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the time she enrolled at Penn she was burned out on the sport.\", \"from\": 3362, \"to\": 3427, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3390, \"end\": 3394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_Jillette\", \"score\": 0.9999999916635716, \"rank\": 8.33601727018006e-09, \"text\": \"Penn\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_Jillette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_Jillette\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Without it, though, she was lacking direction.\", \"from\": 3428, \"to\": 3474, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One night on the way home from a party she came across a group of breakers on campus.\", \"from\": 3475, \"to\": 3560, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They had a club and convinced her to come to a free class a few days later, and she quickly got hooked.\", \"from\": 3561, \"to\": 3664, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe reason I fell in love with it was because it was so different from gymnastics,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Choi says.\", \"from\": 3666, \"to\": 3765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3755, \"end\": 3759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\", \"score\": 0.9996609991704456, \"rank\": 0.00033911578969275864, \"text\": \"Choi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cMy whole life I had been living by this very, very organized list of checked boxes.\", \"from\": 3766, \"to\": 3852, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What I loved about breaking is that it challenged that.\", \"from\": 3853, \"to\": 3908, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It requires you to show up and to figure out who you are and express yourself.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d And no matter how she expressed herself, she was accepted.\", \"from\": 3909, \"to\": 4049, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In that world, she says, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cYou blend in by not fitting in.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\\u00c2  Choi, 35, graduated from college in 2011.\", \"from\": 4050, \"to\": 4156, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4115, \"end\": 4119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\", \"score\": 0.9996609991704456, \"rank\": 0.00033911578969275864, \"text\": \"Choi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She got into marketing, eventually making her way up to global creative operations director for Est\\u00c3\\u00a9e Lauder.\", \"from\": 4157, \"to\": 4267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4260, \"end\": 4266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lauder\", \"score\": 0.99996647881904, \"rank\": 3.352230460325233e-05, \"text\": \"Lauder\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lauder\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lauder\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She kept breaking, working out whenever she could find the time in her busy schedule.\", \"from\": 4268, \"to\": 4353, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For 10 years she deftly moved between two worlds, one corporate, one hip-hop.\", \"from\": 4354, \"to\": 4431, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After the IOC announced in 2020 that breaking would be added to the program in Paris, Choi used it as motivation to go all in.\", \"from\": 4432, \"to\": 4558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4442, \"end\": 4445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.661784424307195e-32, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 4511, \"end\": 4516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2571388585080665e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4518, \"end\": 4522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\", \"score\": 0.9996609991704456, \"rank\": 0.00033911578969275864, \"text\": \"Choi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She quit her job, becoming B-Girl Sunny full-time.\", \"from\": 4559, \"to\": 4609, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Soon Choi was ranked in the world\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s top 10.\", \"from\": 4611, \"to\": 4656, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She clinched her spot in the Olympics when she won gold at the 2023 Pan Am Games.\", \"from\": 4657, \"to\": 4738, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(A country can send up to two B-Girls and two B-Boys; the other U.S. competitor who directly qualified is Victor Montalvo.)\", \"from\": 4739, \"to\": 4862, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4845, \"end\": 4851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"score\": 0.9999995574217861, \"rank\": 4.425715763630689e-07, \"text\": \"Victor\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\"}, {\"begin\": 4852, \"end\": 4860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Ventura_station\", \"score\": 0.9769238581102762, \"rank\": 0.02362122871543744, \"text\": \"Montalvo\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Ventura_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Ventura_station\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Like Choi, Canada\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s B-Boy Philip Kim, who also earned a \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009923 Pan Am Games gold medal, stumbled into the sport by chancing upon some breakers.\", \"from\": 4864, \"to\": 5008, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4869, \"end\": 4873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\", \"score\": 0.9996609991704456, \"rank\": 0.00033911578969275864, \"text\": \"Choi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\"}, {\"begin\": 4892, \"end\": 4902, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Kim\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Philip Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Kim\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Kim\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Kim\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s case, it was outside an art museum in his hometown of Vancouver.\", \"from\": 5009, \"to\": 5084, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5074, \"end\": 5083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6432235336895822e-23, \"text\": \"Vancouver\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Replicating the crew\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s moves gave the middle schooler an outlet for his ample energy.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI was super into anime and so were a lot of my friends,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he says.\", \"from\": 5085, \"to\": 5245, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cSo we would make up characters and play at recess.\", \"from\": 5246, \"to\": 5299, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I did the same at home.\", \"from\": 5300, \"to\": 5327, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My parents remember me running around in my underwear at home, pretending to be Goku or Spider-Man.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  By the time he was in ninth grade, his classmates had dubbed him B-Boy Kimchi.\", \"from\": 5328, \"to\": 5510, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5408, \"end\": 5412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Goku\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Goku\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Goku\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Goku\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(He\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s since adopted a new moniker: Phil Wizard, the surname coming from a crew he used to be a part of.)\", \"from\": 5511, \"to\": 5617, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Becoming a professional was a no-brainer, and not just because he\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s good (he was the 2022 world champion).\", \"from\": 5618, \"to\": 5726, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His career allows him to connect with those superhero days.\", \"from\": 5727, \"to\": 5786, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cFor me, now, breaking is reminiscent of that in a way, because I just kind of travel the world, doing dance battles,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he says.\", \"from\": 5787, \"to\": 5918, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Breaking has always had a competitive element.\", \"from\": 5920, \"to\": 5966, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIf you were poor, you got your best clothes on and your best cologne, you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re styling,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d says Michael Chambers, a B-Boy known as Boogaloo Shrimp and one of the stars of 1984\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099sBreakin\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099and its sequel.\", \"from\": 5967, \"to\": 6174, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6066, \"end\": 6082, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Chambers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Michael Chambers\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Chambers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Chambers\"}, {\"begin\": 6101, \"end\": 6109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boogaloo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.512552468237305e-28, \"text\": \"Boogaloo\", \"types\": [\"Q188451\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boogaloo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boogaloo\"}, {\"begin\": 6110, \"end\": 6116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shrimp\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.986671515728482e-17, \"text\": \"Shrimp\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shrimp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shrimp\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIf you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re styling and you ain\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t got much money and you took a bus to the club, you could still be the king of the city if you had the right talent.\", \"from\": 6175, \"to\": 6329, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The battling thing was like,O.K., I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m going to bruise your ego.\", \"from\": 6330, \"to\": 6395, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I may be broke, but I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m no joke.\", \"from\": 6396, \"to\": 6430, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Watch this.\", \"from\": 6431, \"to\": 6442, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Boom!\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d (It bears noting that Chambers, who last year put out a kids book calledLil\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 Boogaloo Shrimp and the Clean Sweep,would like to be the Charles Barkley of breaking.)\", \"from\": 6443, \"to\": 6617, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6531, \"end\": 6539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boogaloo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.512552468237305e-28, \"text\": \"Boogaloo\", \"types\": [\"Q188451\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boogaloo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boogaloo\"}, {\"begin\": 6540, \"end\": 6546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shrimp\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.986671515728482e-17, \"text\": \"Shrimp\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shrimp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shrimp\"}, {\"begin\": 6588, \"end\": 6603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Barkley\", \"score\": 0.9999999469573609, \"rank\": 5.304280597342251e-08, \"text\": \"Charles Barkley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Barkley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Barkley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Chambers and fellow breaker Adolfo Qui\\u00c3\\u00b1ones threw down against the Electro Rock on film (with a young Ice-T as the DJ), the people in the room decided who won, crowning the winner by acclamation.\", \"from\": 6619, \"to\": 6820, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The sport of Olympic breaking is a wholly different animal.\", \"from\": 6821, \"to\": 6880, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The competitors face off head-to-head, alternating turns in a series of three throw downs, each of which can last up to a minute.\", \"from\": 6882, \"to\": 7011, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A panel of judges declares the winner.\", \"from\": 7012, \"to\": 7050, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are no required moves and while it is literally dancing, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s rarely choreographed.\", \"from\": 7051, \"to\": 7142, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI only plan about 20 to 30% of a round,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d says Choi.\", \"from\": 7143, \"to\": 7199, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7194, \"end\": 7198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\", \"score\": 0.9996609991704456, \"rank\": 0.00033911578969275864, \"text\": \"Choi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cBut even then, sometimes that goes out the window and I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll change it right on the spot.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Montalvo, 30, who competes as B-Boy Victor, will plan out three signature moves in each throw down.\", \"from\": 7200, \"to\": 7396, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7297, \"end\": 7305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Ventura_station\", \"score\": 0.9769238581102762, \"rank\": 0.02362122871543744, \"text\": \"Montalvo\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Ventura_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Ventura_station\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI try to keep myself 50% structured and then 50% improvised,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he says.\", \"from\": 7397, \"to\": 7472, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Part of that improvisation is going with the flow, but there\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s also a strategic element at play.\", \"from\": 7474, \"to\": 7572, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cOften times I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m responding to the opponent,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d says Kim.\", \"from\": 7573, \"to\": 7634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7630, \"end\": 7633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.772231935382135e-20, \"text\": \"Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIn breaking we often talk about having a conversation with movement.\", \"from\": 7635, \"to\": 7706, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If someone does a move but I have a better variation of it, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s also showing the judges,Look, he\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s adapting in the moment.\", \"from\": 7707, \"to\": 7834, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s also showing that he\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s listening to the opponent.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\\u00c2  Kim has an especially deep repertoire of moves\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094avocabulary, in the sport\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s parlance\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094which makes him tough to beat, since judges are on the lookout for a variety of techniques, including:  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cYou\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re using every muscle in your body, basically, in a way that you don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t in your everyday life,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d says Choi.\", \"from\": 7835, \"to\": 8211, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7899, \"end\": 7902, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.772231935382135e-20, \"text\": \"Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\"}, {\"begin\": 8206, \"end\": 8210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\", \"score\": 0.9996609991704456, \"rank\": 0.00033911578969275864, \"text\": \"Choi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cYou\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re not just walking on your feet.\", \"from\": 8212, \"to\": 8254, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re upside down, you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re rotating, you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re spinning, you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re sliding.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  That means that in addition to dance work, there\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a lot of time spent in the gym.\", \"from\": 8255, \"to\": 8421, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s usually a combination of strength training, explosive work, high intensity interval training\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094things that will help my breaking as well as exercises that will work the antagonist muscles,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d says Kim.\", \"from\": 8422, \"to\": 8633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8629, \"end\": 8632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.772231935382135e-20, \"text\": \"Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cBreaking is a lot of push movements.\", \"from\": 8634, \"to\": 8673, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So I will incorporate a lot of pull movements into my workouts so that I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m not imbalanced with my body.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  While the goal of a breaker is to exert total control over their body, there\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s one thing they have zero control of: the music.\", \"from\": 8674, \"to\": 8912, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlike gymnasts or figure skaters, who arrive with predetermined music, B-Boys and B-Girls are at the mercy of the DJ, who picks the tunes.\", \"from\": 8913, \"to\": 9052, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9028, \"end\": 9030, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.552224740717365e-14, \"text\": \"DJ\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only thing competitors know ahead of time is a rough range of beats per minute.\", \"from\": 9053, \"to\": 9136, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not only does the music selection make preparation tricky, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s also a source of controversy.\", \"from\": 9138, \"to\": 9233, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Paris, because of copyright laws, you won\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t hear any old-school hip-hop, which feeds into the main argument by critics of breaking\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s inclusion in the Olympics: that not enough is done to connect the sport to its roots, especially when it will draw millions of eyeballs.\", \"from\": 9234, \"to\": 9510, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9237, \"end\": 9242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2571388585080665e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gabriel Dionisio, better known as Kwikstep, grew up breaking in New York City in the 1980s.\", \"from\": 9512, \"to\": 9603, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9576, \"end\": 9589, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8953911353772197e-34, \"text\": \"New York City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He finds himself frustrated by way the sport is being presented.\", \"from\": 9604, \"to\": 9668, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m excited by [the Olympics] and its potential of exposing breaking further to the world,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he says.\", \"from\": 9669, \"to\": 9776, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWhat I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m concerned with is the lack of cultural representation.\", \"from\": 9777, \"to\": 9845, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Its origins, where it comes from.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  With his wife, Ana Garcia (the groundbreaking B-Girl Rokafella), Dionisio runs a non-profit, Full Circle Productions, that procures grant money from the likes of the Ford Foundation and the Mellon Foundation.\", \"from\": 9846, \"to\": 10092, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9903, \"end\": 9909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jerry_Garcia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.4514227062785e-29, \"text\": \"Garcia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jerry_Garcia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jerry_Garcia\"}, {\"begin\": 9977, \"end\": 9988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Full_Circle_(novel)\", \"score\": 0.5255999370944305, \"rank\": 0.35693039857221487, \"text\": \"Full Circle\", \"types\": [\"Q571\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Full_Circle_(novel)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Full_Circle_(novel)\"}, {\"begin\": 10050, \"end\": 10065, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ford_Foundation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ford Foundation\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ford_Foundation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ford_Foundation\"}, {\"begin\": 10074, \"end\": 10091, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_W._Mellon_Foundation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mellon Foundation\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_W._Mellon_Foundation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_W._Mellon_Foundation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They use the funds to help put on shows and to educate young people about the roots of breaking.\", \"from\": 10093, \"to\": 10189, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ahead of an event Dionisio will make sure the MC knows the stories of any old school B-Boys who are there, and he sets up a booth where crews can put up old photos.\", \"from\": 10190, \"to\": 10354, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cNow it has a social context,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he says.\", \"from\": 10355, \"to\": 10398, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ken Gabbert is a little more blunt.\", \"from\": 10400, \"to\": 10435, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As Ken Swift, he was a pioneering member of the Rock Steady Crew.\", \"from\": 10436, \"to\": 10501, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10443, \"end\": 10448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonathan_Swift\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.389421976939505e-19, \"text\": \"Swift\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonathan_Swift\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonathan_Swift\"}, {\"begin\": 10484, \"end\": 10500, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rock_Steady_Crew\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rock Steady Crew\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rock_Steady_Crew\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rock_Steady_Crew\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s not a sport,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he says.\", \"from\": 10502, \"to\": 10536, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAn art form that we created with our own terminology and heritage and tradition, all of a sudden for an opportunity, we start calling ourselves athletes and calling this art a sport?\", \"from\": 10537, \"to\": 10722, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s like saying, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098Let\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s call basketball a dance now after 75 years.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 As a part of a culture, I look at it from a different perspective.\", \"from\": 10723, \"to\": 10869, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I look at it artistically, as something that we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve sustained for 50 years to get to this point.\", \"from\": 10870, \"to\": 10967, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI love sports.\", \"from\": 10969, \"to\": 10986, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I get that.\", \"from\": 10987, \"to\": 10998, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But when I was breaking, the whole aspect of doing stuff with my body\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094the type of freedom, really connecting to drums and music\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094was different for me.\", \"from\": 10999, \"to\": 11152, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So right now I see what\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s happening.\", \"from\": 11153, \"to\": 11191, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A lot of people act like I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m a hater, but they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re wrong.\", \"from\": 11192, \"to\": 11252, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s just that I have a culture I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m a part of called hip-hop, and it ain\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t going to change.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Holman\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094who speaks passionately about the community-building and storytelling power of breaking\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094sees both sides of the argument.\", \"from\": 11253, \"to\": 11486, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ultimately he\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s in favor of the Olympics (he petitioned to have breaking included in 1984), but he does have concerns about where the sport is headed.\", \"from\": 11487, \"to\": 11639, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cA lot of these new jack, young breakers, many of them are these incredible gymnasts,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he says.\", \"from\": 11640, \"to\": 11739, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s not just gymnastics, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s also gyroscopic control over your own body.\", \"from\": 11740, \"to\": 11821, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re doing these moves that are just out of this world.\", \"from\": 11822, \"to\": 11886, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But are they dancing to the music?\", \"from\": 11887, \"to\": 11921, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cYou see them going into their routine and they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re on beat, but then they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re going into these moves that are living in their own time and space and have nothing to do with the beats and the rhythm and the melody and the energy and the emotional power of the song and of the music.\", \"from\": 11923, \"to\": 12209, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re just doing these moves and challenging someone else to do a move as powerful.\", \"from\": 12210, \"to\": 12297, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t even need music to do it.\", \"from\": 12298, \"to\": 12335, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If your routine can just be done without music, then that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s not breaking.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Most young breakers are attuned to the discussion.\", \"from\": 12336, \"to\": 12466, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Montalvo, whose father and uncle were B-Boys in Mexico, says he doesn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t really like dancing to the music at competitions: \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009c\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0089\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098Apache\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 [by the Incredible Bongo Band] or James Brown\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098Break It Loose\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 remix?\", \"from\": 12467, \"to\": 12687, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12515, \"end\": 12521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\", \"score\": 0.9999999999845386, \"rank\": 1.4910217175122413e-11, \"text\": \"Mexico\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You put those on and that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll have us dancing all night.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Choi, who aspires to open a dance and community center in Queens, says one thing she doesn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t like in her role as B-Girl Sunny is doing press.\", \"from\": 12688, \"to\": 12893, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12750, \"end\": 12754, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\", \"score\": 0.9996609991704456, \"rank\": 0.00033911578969275864, \"text\": \"Choi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Choi_Eun-hee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, she says, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI do it a lot to share about breaking and the community, about the culture.\", \"from\": 12894, \"to\": 12987, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t have breaking without hip-hop.\", \"from\": 12988, \"to\": 13030, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t have breaking without the culture.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a point echoed by Kim, but being a 27-year-old Canadian means he doesn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t have the personal experience of the old school, which in turn means he\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll more readily accept an evolution.\", \"from\": 13031, \"to\": 13273, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13107, \"end\": 13110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.772231935382135e-20, \"text\": \"Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt comes from Black and Latino culture,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d he says.\", \"from\": 13274, \"to\": 13328, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13291, \"end\": 13296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Americans\", \"score\": 0.999983951258944, \"rank\": 1.6048998887030256e-05, \"text\": \"Black\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Americans\"}, {\"begin\": 13301, \"end\": 13307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Music_of_Latin_America\", \"score\": 0.9985606560896199, \"rank\": 0.0014413042516276525, \"text\": \"Latino\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Music_of_Latin_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Music_of_Latin_America\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThat\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s the roots of where it came from.\", \"from\": 13329, \"to\": 13373, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I think it also speaks on the beauty of where breaking and hip-hop in general can go.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  One place breaking, ironically, won\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t go is back to the Olympics.\", \"from\": 13374, \"to\": 13535, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s not on the docket for the 2028 Games, a head-scratching decision by the IOC given that they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re to be held in Los Angeles, one of the hotbeds of the early days of the art form.\", \"from\": 13536, \"to\": 13720, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13615, \"end\": 13618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.661784424307195e-32, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 13654, \"end\": 13665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.711051485190682e-30, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Keeping it on the program would give the sport a chance to grow its popularity further and maybe a second appearance, one without the novelty that comes with a debut, would mean more time could be spent on discussing the history.\", \"from\": 13721, \"to\": 13950, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And breaking has always had a way of delivering memorable sequels.\", \"from\": 13951, \"to\": 14017, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2  Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 14018, \"to\": 14047, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Mark Bechtel has been a writer and editor at Sports Illustrated for 30 years.\", \"from\": 14048, \"to\": 14189, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14117, \"end\": 14124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bechtel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bechtel\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bechtel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bechtel\"}, {\"begin\": 14157, \"end\": 14175, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.844513329255409e-32, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s covered a variety of sports, including baseball, auto racing, soccer and\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094his favorite\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094curling, as well as contributing to the magazine\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s media coverage.\", \"from\": 14190, \"to\": 14355, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC.\", \"from\": 14357, \"to\": 14434, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"- All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 14435, \"to\": 14457, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only.\", \"from\": 14458, \"to\": 14534, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Sports Illustrated or its affiliates, licensees and related brands.\", \"from\": 14535, \"to\": 14729, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14662, \"end\": 14680, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.844513329255409e-32, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit.\", \"from\": 14730, \"to\": 14818, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\", \"from\": 14819, \"to\": 14951, \"entities\": []}]}"